16/03/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- President Behgjet Pacolli is asking NATO countries to train the highest ranking Kosovo Security Force (KSF) officials in their academies. Pacolli thanked NATO for its contribution in Kosovo and its role in establishing and training the KSF during a meeting Tuesday (March 15th) with Admiral Samuel J. Locklear, NATO's Commander of Allied Joint Force Command Naples and KFOR Commander Erhard Buehler. Locklear said that he has noticed positive changes during his visits to Kosovo over the last six months. KFOR downsizing, he added "does not reduce KFOR's role in Kosovo". (Kohavision, RTK, TV 21, Klan Kosova - 15/03/11)
